The paper discusses algorithmic approaches for the design and management of vehicle-sharing systems, which involves optimization and decision-making problems. This makes it likely to belong to the Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA) and Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science (cs.CE) sub-categories. The paper also mentions customer incentivisation schemes and cost-effective solutions, which may involve machine learning and optimization techniques, making it possible to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG), Information Theory (cs.IT), and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-categories.
